&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Staff Nurse - Respiratory Wards&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The respiratory wards are looking for band 5 registered nurses to work on our busy acute inpatient areas, Ward 22 and Ward 23, based at Aintree Hospital. We specialise in caring for general medical patients with acute and chronic respiratory diseases. The wards routinely treat patients with a variety of conditions such as asthma, COPD, bronchiectasis, pulmonary embolism and pneumothorax’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are many opportunities to become proficient in managing patients with long term conditions, chest drains, tracheostomies and care for patient on high flow oxygen and non-invasive ventilation. The ward is very acute and busy but we support and train staff within our dedicated teams to become proficient in the management of a variety of conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide teaching in (but not limited to): Non-invasive ventilation, AIRVO Chest drains (standard and digital) &amp; pleurodesis Tracheostomy management, ABG sampling and interpretation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our respiratory wards provide an excellent service to our patients working collaboratively with our respiratory Consultants, respiratory Nurse Specialist, Advanced Nurse Practitioners, Chest Physios and Community Respiratory Nurses to ensure our patients receive excellent care and a safe discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Aintree offer a comprehensive 4 week Education programme prior to commencing on the ward covering clinical and non-clinical study sessions and at least 2 week supernumerary shadowing an experience Registered Nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fantastic opportunity to gain acute clinical skills and experience in this field of nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**PLEASE NOTE THAT THIS VACANCY IS FOR REGISTERED NURSES. IF YOU ARE A STUDENT NURSE, PLEASE CONTACT THE RECRUITMENT TEAM ON 0151 529 3030**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Louise Walsh, Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: louise.walsh@liverpoolft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number0151 529 3438&lt;/p&gt;
